==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anhydrite
<hw>An*hy"drite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Anhydrous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a white
or a slightly bluish color, usually massive. It is anhydrous sulphate of
lime, and differs from gypsum in not containing water (whence the
name).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anhydrous</ent>⟦br⟧
